{
  "stem": "10862.4",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And her mother had survived a war in a camp.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Her mother had found out that this little girl is in that orphanage in Poland, in Lublin, came looking for this little girl.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But meanwhile, my sister, Eda, and my brother had been already taken out of the orphanage.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were going to West Germany.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were taking him to the American side, and they left me behind.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But my other sister, my married sisters, were still in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they had said to me they didn't want me to go, you know, with the-- with the ca-- with the orphanage to Germany, because I was alone.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But meanwhile, they too were thinking of leaving Poland, because Poland was not the place to be.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "It was a hateful country.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They were not very nice to us, and we just didn't want to live there anymore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It was-- you know, you were a person without a country.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Poland really was not your country.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You had nowhere to go.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "So they all decided to go to Germany, with the American, on the West-- with the Americans.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And finally, they came to take the whole orphanage, and I decided to go with them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And I went where my sister and my brother were, to the-- in Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "But in order for me to go there, they couldn't take the whole orphanage out, so they had to individually take you.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So when this woman came looking at the orphanage for her little girl, my sisters had asked this woman to please bring me with.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She says, please, she's my little sister.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Why don't you take her with?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So the woman said to them, OK.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "If it's not going to be too difficult for you, we will take her with.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
